-- France’s Moscovici Says No Plan to Extend Ads on Public TV
-- B y   F r a n c o i s   d e   B e a u p u y
-- 2012-06-03T17:36:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-03/france-s-moscovici-says-no-plan-to-extend-ads-on-public-tv.html
French Finance Minister Pierre
Moscovici said he hasn’t heard of any plans to reintroduce
advertising on public television beyond 8 p.m.  “I haven’t considered it and haven’t seen serious documents
with respect to that,” Moscovici said on RTL radio today. “I
haven’t seen” such a plan, he said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Francois de Beaupuy at 
 fdebeaupuy@bloomberg.net  